cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.THEORY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a logic whose formulas specify behavioural properties. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper investigates behavioural equivalence between programs in a functional language extended with a signature of effect-triggering operations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with specifying and verifying behavioural properties of software programs. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper uses formal methods to define and reason about behavioural equivalence. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is also a possible category as the paper presents a general theory of modalities expressing effect-specific aspects of behaviour.
